sec.p:
The total shoot pixel area derived from the three RGB images were used to calculate the projected shoot area (PSA, kpixels) of each plant (Golzarian et al. 2011; Rajendran et al. 2009). A linear correlation between shoot biomass and PSA has been observed in Triticum monococcum (Golzarian et al. 2011) and bread wheat (Takahashi et al. 2015). To calculate the growth rate of an individual plant, a cubic smoothing spline was fitted to the PSA for the plant as measured over time, using the R function smooth.splines with degrees of freedom (df) set to 4 (Al-Tamimi et al. 2016). The relative growth rate (RGR) was calculated for each plant for each day it was imaged as RGR \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
